narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: perspective on the world of academic peer review and the methods and process necessary for creating a peer-reviewed paper for publication in an appropriate journal
I developed the skills of writing a scientific paper, choosing the appropriate statistical analysis, and presenting.

narratives.question_text: How well did the knowledge, skills, and insights gained in this class align with your expectations?
comments: I gained what I expected since I sat in this class last year.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of the course and how could it be improved?
comments: strengths: small class size and intensive practice on speaking about and formally presenting your own research
We could probably spend more time on data analysis and rumination.

narratives.question_text: What advice would you give to a student considering taking this class?
comments: be prepared to be criticized, in a good way and in a healthy and encouraging environment
It would be preferable if you know R and multivariate statistics. They help you with your data analysis. Prepare to read a lot of literature.
